f=Engineering/axiom/custom/algorithm-review/SKILL.md · in=algorithm-review axiom's specialist read change's algorithmic content correctness, complexity, edge cases, numerical stability pass dev's code-review-standards routes diff contains non-trivial algorithmic logic, routes security-risky diffs aegis. It's axiom's rigor reaches code axiom didn't write. · p=Normal review checks "does work examples." Algorithmic review checks "is correct inputs, scale, handle cases examples miss" off-by-ones, empty/singleton/huge inputs, integer overflow, floating-point accumulation, O(n²) hiding nested comprehension. bugs pass tests fail production. · wu=Triggers: dev's code-review routing algorithm-heavy diff here, "review algorithm," "is correct," "will scale," sorting/search/graph/numeric code, any change structure covered dsa-design-record. · st:/ Protocol=`Algorithm-heavy diff arrives (dev routing / self-flagged) \· -> CORRECTNESS: does it compute the right thing for ALL inputs, not just the examples? \· invariants hold? termination guaranteed (no infinite loop/recursion)? \· -> EDGE CASES: empty \· singleton \· duplicate \· sorted/reverse \· huge \· overflow \· NaN/precision \· -> COMPLEXITY: time/space via complexity-analysis; regression vs the prior version? (flag)` · in=**Correctness inputs.** Trace invariant termination condition, sample run. algorithm that's right test cases wrong empty input wrong. Prove invariant holds across loop/recursion, find breaks. **Hunt edge cases tests skip.** Empty, singleton, all-duplicate, already-sorted, reverse-sorted, maximum-size, integer overflow boundaries, floating-point accumulation NaN. algorithmic bugs live; green test suite omits them proves little (ties quinn's meaningful-assertion rule). **Check complexity, flag regressions.** Run complexity-analysis change; worsens hot path's class versus prior version, that's finding even passing tests (small-n tests hide it). **Structure drift finding.** dsa-design-record covers structure change contradicts (uses operation it's bad at, swaps without new record), flag drift either record needs updating new DSR) code off-design (dev's stack-drift rule, algorithm edition). **Findings actionable.** `file:line what's wrong fix`, failing input complexity delta evidence discipline dev's aegis's reviews. **Don't gold-plate.** correct, adequately-fast algorithm cold path doesn't need axiom's ideal structure; flag real problems, absence theoretical perfection (dev's don't-block-on-taste). · of=`## Algorithm Review: [change] — routed by [dev ref] \· Correctness: [pass / findings — invariant/termination] \· Edge cases: [checked list / gaps] \· Complexity: [bound \· regression vs prior? ] \· DSR fit: [matches / drift → DSR-ref] \·  \· ### Verdict: SOUND / FINDINGS  (→ dev review + quinn gate)` · pr=**Correct inputs** invariants termination, sample runs., **The edge cases bugs** empty/huge/overflow/precision; green tests skip them prove little., **Complexity regressions findings** small-n tests won't catch worsened class., **Structure drift finding** off-design code stale record; resolve which., **Findings actionable evidence** failing input delta., **Don't gold-plate cold paths** flag real problems, missing perfection. · f=dsa-design-record structure review universal correctness/complexity grounds; structure load-bearing, recommend record created., Correctness genuinely hard prove (heuristic/approximate algorithm) state what's guaranteed best-effort, require tests pin guaranteed properties (route quinn)., Diff large rigorous algorithmic review request split rather skim (dev's over-broad-diff concern). · b:with Other Skills=**dev/code-review-standards**: routes algorithm-heavy diffs here, way routes security aegis; specialist depth, replacement dev's per-PR review., **complexity-analysis dsa-design-records** (siblings): supply bounds design-of-record review checks against., **aegis/secure-code-review**: security-side parallel; worst-case-complexity finding enables DoS aegis's concern (cross-route)., **quinn**: findings feed gate; algorithmic fragile areas become regression-map entries.